Company Description: Eugene Water & Electric Board, Also Known As Eweb, Is One Of The Largest Public Utility Companies IN Oregon. Chartered By The City Of Eugene As A Municipal Utility With A Separate Elected Board, Eweb Provides Electricity, Water And Steam To More Than 83,000 Homes, Business, Schools And Other Customers IN Eugene, Ore. Founded IN 1911, The Board, IN Partnership With Other Local Agencies, Offers Assistance To Farmers And Growers IN Disposing Unwanted Chemicals Through Its Agricultural Chemical Program. The Utility Provides More Than $700,000 Annually To Support Education Programs On Energy And Water Resources. It Also Offers Various Recreational Opportunities, From Trails Along The Walterville Power Canal To Boating And Fishing At Carmen Reservoir On The Upper Mckenzie River. The Utility Supports A Variety Of Community Events, Including Eugene Celebration And The Annual Solar Challenge Race For Middle School Students.

Company Description: Heating Homes & Helping Yards.Grimm's Fuel Company Has Been Providing Fuel And Landscape Material Delivery To Business And Residential Customers Within The Portland, OR, Metro Area Since 1930. Our Business Initially Opened With The Singular Goal Of Delivering Home Heating Oil.  Today, Our Team Provides A Variety Of Help To Building Owners, From Furnace Care To Mulch Delivery.  At Grimms Fuel Company, Our Services Include: Fir OR Hemlock Barkdust Garden Mulch Cedar Chips Organic Compost And Topsoil Decorative Rock Furnace And Boiler Repair OR Installation Heating Oil Deliveryfor Those Who Are Not Familiar With Barkdust, It Is An Attractive Landscaping Product That Provides Insulation IN The Colder Months And Helps Plants Retain Their Moisture During The Warmer Months, As Well As Stops Weeds And Improves Soil Drainage. Our Barkdust, As Well As Our Other Landscaping Materials, Is Available By Three Methods: Self-Pick-Up, Delivery OR Delivery With Installation. Grimms Fuel Company Offers Both Medium And Fine Grinds IN Various Shades, From Traditional Red To Dark Brown OR Black Mulch. With Several Locations Throughout The Metro Area, You Can Be Assured That Service Will Be Provided Quickly And Efficiently.  Whether You Are Ordering Heating Oil OR Landscaping Materials, You Wont Be Shivering For Long And Neither Will Your Landscaping.Call Grimms Fuel Company Today For Quick Service OR To Place An Order!

Company Description: Growing Up On The Family Cattle Ranch IN Pilot Rock, Corey Anderson Always Dreamed Of Operating His Own Business. IN 2007 He Did Just That When He Purchased Pendleton Electric Company, The Same Business That He Began His Apprenticeship With IN 1995. After Receiving His Associates From Bmcc IN Automotive Technology Corey Decided To Try Something New And Entered The Electrical Field. By 1999 He Had Worked Up To A Journeyman Electrician After Completing 576 Classroom Hours And Over 8000 Hours On The Job. Corey Continued His Advancement As A Journeyman However He Could Not Be Derailed From His Goal Of Ownership. When An On The Job Injury Could Have Ended His Career He Used It As Another Forward Motion And IN 2000 Stepped Up As A Foreman/Estimator Pendleton Electric Co. He Then Followed That Up With An Advancement To Project Manager IN 2002. Late IN The Summer Of 2005 Corey And His Wife, Mindy, Welcomed Their Fourth Son Into Their Family, And As His Family Grew So Did His Old Desire To Take The Reins Of His Own Company. As 2007 Rolled Around So Did The Opportunity For That Dream To Come True, Corey Began The Process Of Purchasing Pendleton Electric From The Long Time Owners, The Hale & Tullis Families. By January Of 2008, Corey Was The Sole Owner Of The Long Standing Pendleton Business. Deeply Rooted IN Eastern Oregon, Pendleton Electric Was Founded IN 1956 By Bob Hale. Bob Operated The Business Until His Death Upon Which Time His Children Took Over Ownership. They Continued Running The Business Until The Transfer Of Ownership To Corey IN 2007. There Have Been Many Changes IN The Electrical Contracting Business Over The Last 60 Years And P.E. Has Grown Right With Them. It Is The Mission Of Pendleton Electric Company To Provide Dependable, Knowledgeable And Trustworthy Electrical Contracting. We Are Focusing Our Attention IN The Geographical Area To The Commercial And Industrial Customer While Continuing To Provide Our High Level Of Residential Service. We Will Continue To Set The Standard Of Excellence While Raising The Bar Of Quality Through Our Company Employee's Work Ethic, Team Work, Communication And Accountability. Company Description: The Pgg Story    Wintry Weather Cast A Chill Over Pendleton On Saturday, December 21, 1929. The Mood Of The Country Was As Somber As The Gray Clouds IN The Sky That Day. Wheat Prices Kept Sliding. 'wheat Gamblers' Ruled The Market, Critics Said, And Farmers Suffered. Wheat Sold At $1.20 A Bushel IN Portland That Day.    The Shock Of 'black Friday,' October 29, Still Rattled The Economic Foundation Of The United States. Every Time The Stock Market Opened, Prices Dropped. President Hoover Counseled Patience. But People Were Worried And Frightened.    The Alta Theater IN Pendleton That December Night Almost Five Decades Ago Showed A Film Called 'the Racketeer.' It Was Billed As 'a Thrilling, All-Talking Romance Of The Underworld.' Maybe It Was Just What People Needed To Take Their Minds Off The Troubled Times.    But Instead Of Trying To Forget Their Troubles At The Movie, About 100 Umatilla County Wheat Farmers Crowded Into The Pendleton Chamber Of Commerce Office To Hear Roy Ritner, Alva Shumway And James Hill Sr. Talk About A New Hope For Wheat Growers. Pendleton Grain Growers Inc. Was Conceived That Night!     The Farmers Who Made Up Pendleton Grain Growers Board Of Directors During The Cooperative's Early Years May Not Have Seen Themselves As Visionaries, But Hindsight Shows That They Were. The Minutes Of The Board Meetings Of Those Years Show Repeated Comments About The Move To Bulk Handling Of Grain, About The Possibility Of Developing A Way To Use The Columbia River To Transport Grain, About The Possibilities Offered By A Feed Mill, And About The Need For Pendleton Grain Growers To Own Bulk Grain Storage Facilities.    The Year 1938 Proved Pivotal For Pgg. Commitments Were Made And Courses Set That Had Far-Reaching Effects. Even Though Money And Credit Was Tight, Important Decisions Were Made Anyway.    The Board's Interest IN River Shipping Of Grain Continued. The Entire Community Benefited As Pgg Began To Stretch Out! One Of The Most Important Decisions Was The One Of December 3, 1938 To Buy The International Harvester Machinery Franchise From Jackson Implement Company. Taking On The New Endeavor Proved To Have Been The Right Move.    Inovation Continues To Be A Pgg Hallmark. IN 1994, Pgg And Harvest States Formed A New, Limited Liability Company To Operate Feedville. The Name Of The New Firm Is Pgg/Hsc Feed Company. The Latest Example Of Pgg's Enterprise And Forward Thinking Is The Acquisition Of Scott Irrigation Company IN Union County. Because There's A Wide Variance Of Climate And Cropping IN Pgg Country, The Addition Of Scott Irrigation Gave Pgg More Flexibility IN Meeting The Needs Of It's Producers.     As The 21st Century Develops, Pgg Has Positioned It's Posture As A Lean And Tough Company, Ready To Take On The Challenges Of The Industry And Positioned To Compete. The Company That Started IN 1930 With A Handful Of Notes And Lots Of Faith Today Has A Net Worth Of Over $17.5 Million. It Has 2410 Stockholders, 205 Employees, And A Thirst For Success!

Company Description: About Rootx Root Control Corp Manufactures A Foaming Root-Control Chemical For Residential And Municipal Sewer Lines, Storm Pipes And Septic Systems. The Patented Rootx Formula Uses The Aquatic Herbicide Dichlobenil. It's Non-Caustic, Non-Fumigating And Non-Systemic, And It Contains No Diquat Bromide, Copper Sulfate OR Metam Sodium. Rootx Is Classified As A General Use Product By The Environmental Protection Agency, And It Is Registered For Use IN All 50 States ( Epa Registration # 68464-1 ). IN Addition, Rootx Carries The Signal Word Caution, The Lowest Hazard Rating According To The Iso 3864-2 Standard For Hazard Severity Panels. Gelco Introduced The Patented Rootx Formula For Pipeline Root Control IN 1994. It Was Designed To Avoid The Problems Wastewater Treatment Plants Had With Existing Root Control Chemicals As Well As To Promote Worker, Public And Environmental Safety. Rootx Was Also Designed For Fast, Easy Application Without The Extensive Training Required By Other Products. For More Than A Decade, Rootx Has Proven To Be Effective And Cost-Efficient With Customers Throughout The United States. Rootx Has Been Successful Simply Because It Works. Rootx Is Only Sold To Professional Drain Cleaners, Municipal Contractors And Municipal Maintenance Departments. Municipalities Can Apply Rootx As Part Of Their Normal Sewer Maintenance Program Using Their Own Crews And Equipment. Using A 20-Pound Bag Of Rootx, Crews Can Treat A 400-Foot Mainline IN 30 Minutes OR Less. For Professional Drain Cleaners Who Work With Residential Service Laterals And Septic Tanks, Rootx Is Available IN Convenient 2- And 4-Pound Jars. Rootx Is Used By Municipalities And Drain Cleaning Contractors IN All 50 States, And It Is Also Used IN Canada, Israel And Portugal. Rootx Users Include Large Cities Like Fort Lauderdale And Honolulu, As Well As Medium-Size Cities Like Lafayette, LA ( Population 110, 257 ), And Corvallis, OR ( 50, 126 ). Rootx Is Even Cost Effective For Small Towns Like Brewer, ME ( 8, 987 ), And North English, IA ( 1, 010 ). Rootx Is Not Sold Directly To Homeowners. However, Rootx Has An Online Referral Program To Help Homeowners Locate An Authorized Dealer IN Their Area. Products Rootx Currently Offers Four Products: Rootx Root Control Chemical, The Fdu 100 Foam Dispersal Unit, The Rootx Tripod And Rootx Brand Hand Sanitizer Wipes. The Primary Product Is Rootx Itself. It Is A Patented Root Control Formula That Is Guaranteed To Kill Pipeline Roots. The Rootx Formula Contains The Aquatic Herbicide Dichlobenil, Foaming Agents And Degreasing Agents. Rootx Foams On Contact With Water, Filling The Pipe To Reach The Top Where 90 Percent Of The Roots Live. Degreasing Agents Strip Away Grime So The Rootx Herbicide Can Penetrate The Roots. Rootx Kills Roots On Contact, And It Leaves A Barrier On The Pipe Walls To Prevent Re-Growth. Dead Roots Decay Over Time And Are Carried Away By The Flow Of The Line. Rootx Is Non-Systemic, So It Only Kills The Root Tissue It Comes IN Contact With ; It Does Not Harm Above-Ground Vegetation. IN Addition, Rootx Is Non-Caustic And Non-Fumigating, So It Is Easier For Crews To Handle, And It Has No Adverse Effects On Pipes OR Wastewater Treatment Plants.

Company Description: West Oregon Electric Cooperative ( Woec ) Is Owned By The Members We Serve And Is Committed To Providing Reliable Electricity At The Lowest Price Possible For The Territory We Serve. West Oregon Electric Is A 'not For Profit' Cooperative, And Provides Electricity To Areas That Other Companies Would Not Serve Due To The Rough Terrain And Large Areas With Small Population.Electric Cooperatives Were Created By Determined Customers Who Needed Power IN Rural Areas. With The Help Of Franklin D. Roosevelt, Who Established The Rural Electrification Administration ( Rea ) IN 1935, Friends And Neighbors Banded Together To Create A New Kind Of Electric Utility, Where The Voice Of Every Person Made A Difference. These Electric Cooperatives That Were Formed Brought Electric Power To The Countryside When No One Else Would. That Is How Woec Was Formed IN 1944 To Start Providing Electricity To Areas That Had Been Without Power.Woec Is A Member Of National Rural Electric Cooperative Association ( Nreca ), Oregon Rural Electric Cooperative Association ( Oreca ), And Is Touchstone Energy Cooperative.

Company Description: Through Internal Growth And More Than 320 Acquisitions, Airgas Has Built A National Packaged Gas Distribution Network That Includes More Than 900 Branch Locations, Cylinder Fill Plants, Production Facilities, Specialty Gas Laboratories And Regional Distribution Centers. Airgas Specializes IN The Distribution Of Industrial, Medical And Specialty Gases, As Well As Related Hard Goods Such As Welding Supplies. It Also Distributes Nitrous Oxide, Dry Ice, Liquid Carbon Dioxide, Process Chemicals, Refrigerants And Ammonia Products. Airgas Markets Its Products Through Multiple Channels, Including Its Own Branches And An Outside Sales Force; A Strategic Accounts Team Focused On Large Customers; And Distributors, Resellers, Telesales, Catalogs And Electronic Business Channels. Founded IN 1982, Airgas Maintains Its Headquarters IN Radnor, Pa.
